The EM error is clear: the BPEL deployed successfully, but at runtime it cannot find an enabled config row:

No enabled SewerAI config row found for PROCESS_NAME=IvaraToSewerAI

This happened inside EncodeAndSetOpaquePayload, before it sent to SewerAI.

Run this first:

SELECT *
FROM CUSTOMERDATA.EPSEWERAI_SYNC_CONFIG;

Then make sure you have exactly this kind of row:

MERGE INTO CUSTOMERDATA.EPSEWERAI_SYNC_CONFIG c
USING (
    SELECT
        'IvaraToSewerAI' AS process_name,
        'your-account-sid-here' AS account_sid,
        'X-SAI your-api-key-here' AS api_authorization,
        'Y' AS is_enabled
    FROM dual
) x
ON (c.process_name = x.process_name)
WHEN MATCHED THEN UPDATE SET
    c.account_sid = x.account_sid,
    c.api_authorization = x.api_authorization,
    c.is_enabled = x.is_enabled
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN INSERT (
    process_name,
    account_sid,
    api_authorization,
    is_enabled
) VALUES (
    x.process_name,
    x.account_sid,
    x.api_authorization,
    x.is_enabled
);

COMMIT;

Then test:

SELECT ACCOUNT_SID,
       API_AUTHORIZATION
FROM CUSTOMERDATA.EPSEWERAI_SYNC_CONFIG
WHERE PROCESS_NAME = 'IvaraToSewerAI'
  AND IS_ENABLED = 'Y';

If this returns zero rows, that is the exact reason for the EM error.

Also check capitalization/spaces:

SELECT '[' || PROCESS_NAME || ']' AS process_name_check,
       '[' || IS_ENABLED || ']' AS enabled_check
FROM CUSTOMERDATA.EPSEWERAI_SYNC_CONFIG;

Most likely issue: your table row has a different PROCESS_NAME, or IS_ENABLED is not exactly Y.
